<subSubSection pageId="731" pageNumber="732" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="731" pageNumber="732">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="731" pageNumber="732">This Holarctic species is found in the New World from west-central Alaska south to central California and to southern New Mexico along the Rocky Mountains. Disjunct populations are also known from Chiapas in Mexico and Guatemala [see Liebherr 1991b: Fig. 230]. In the Old World, the species is known from disjunct populations in Lapland, the Austrian Alps, and Burma [see Liebherr 1991b: Fig. 231].</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
